file=AI & Agents/forge/operational/tool/forge-tool-requirements.md · f—t:forge — Tool Requirements=**This file specifies needs; it does not grant them.** Access is configured at deployment (operator/platform; Fleet Charter Rails 1–2 apply).\n · tb=\| Skill \| Needs \| Why \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| model-technique-registry \| file read/write (own registry asset) \| inventory + frontier \| · tb=\| benchmarking-discipline \| eval-run dispatch (platform-dependent); golden-set read; file write (own reports) \| measured comparisons \| · tb=\| technique-adoption \| file read (sources, registry); benchmark dispatch via above \| the gate \| · tb=\| degradation-diagnosis \| read-only: gauge bundles, relay registry, proposal history, version stamps \| timeline + differential \| · f—t:forge — Tool Requirements=forge is read-only toward everything it diagnoses and recommends about — its only writes are its own registry and reports.\n